!Ärgerliche Bugs

!!Guides from Master Pages disappear from page

* create a document (double page) with three pages
* create a new master page
* define guides in master page
* apply the master page to page two
* go to page three
* the guides on the previous page disappear
* open the master page editor
* close it
* the guides are there again and won't disappear when changing page again

resolved: http://bugs.scribus.net/view.php?id=9475

!!Guides from Masterpages misplaced after file opening

* create a new file double sided with three pages, inside margin 5cm, outside margin 1cm
* create two master pages "a" for left and "b" for right with 5 columns guides relative to the margins, with 5mm gap
* by using "apply master pages" apply the "a" master page to the even pages and the "b" one to the odd pages
* the first page has the "b" master page but the guides are not shown on it.
* edit master pages, select "b", manage guides, change reference to page and back to margin, close the manage guides dialog and leave the master pages editor
* the first page now has the guides
* close and reopen the file
* add 2 pages, with "a" MP on the left and "b" on the right
* page 4 has no guides, page 5 has the guides
* open the master pages editor, the "a" MP has the wrong (well the "b") guides, select the "b" MP and it's ok, back to the "a" MP it's ok
* close the MP editor
* the 4th page has guides

resolved: http://bugs.scribus.net/view.php?id=9476

!!scribus crashes when modiying a font path
Description	* open scribus with no file
* add a path in the font preferences
* restart scribus (no file open)
* go the the preferences
* choose the previously created font path
* click on change
* choose the parent directory
* ok
* crash

resolved: http://bugs.scribus.net/view.php?id=9477

